body.title: Nike Air Force 1 High WMNS
body.description: Playing on the classic silhouette of the High-cut original, the Nike Air Force I Sage High women’s shoe takes things up a notch with a wedge midsole and a synthetic leather upper that extends all the way up the calf. Adding to its bold irreverence, removable design details let you tailor the shoe to your own unique style.

body.title: Nike Air Force 1 Rebel XX WMNS
body.description: Refusing to play by traditional design rules, this new edition of the streetwear staple was boasts corset lacing up the back and big stitch details.

body.title: Nike Air Force 1 Jester XX High WMNS
body.description: With the January launch of the 1 Reimagined Collection, the sneaker savvy were treated to five fresh angles on the Air Force 1. Thanks to an elevated sole and whimsical, off-center branding, the Jester gave the streetwear legend a lighthearted feel. The latest edition plays up the Jester persona even more, featuring new colors in a high-top silhouette.

body.title: Nike Air Force 1 Jester XX High WMNS
body.description: With the January launch of the 1 Reimagined Collection, the sneaker savvy were treated to five fresh angles on the Air Force 1. Thanks to an elevated sole and whimsical, off-center branding, the Jester gave the streetwear legend a lighthearted feel. The latest edition plays up the Jester persona even more featuring new colors in a high-top silhouette.

body.title: Nike Kyrie 5
body.description: As part DJ, part hooper, partial skater, and part “unofficial mayor of LA”, Taco has never been one to conform to the world’s standards. Embracing Kyrie’s mantra of “Just Be You”, Taco believes it’s better to be yourself than be who others think you should be. In collaboration with Travis “Taco” Bennett, the Kyrie 5 'Taco PE' is designed to inspire and encourage you to be confident in what makes you, you.

body.title: Nike SB Dunk Low x Diamond Supply
Nike Air Max 97
body.description: Gold projects an energy of decadence and distinction unlike any metal on Earth. This special edition of the iconic Air Max 97 strikes the perfect balance with its precious shine, complimenting it with Black for a powerful look. In the dark, it still shines; the Black, top half of the upper features reflective elements to ensure standing out is never off the table.

body.title: Nike Air Max 97
body.description: Humans have been ravenous for silver since prehistoric times. Sure, it has lots of useful properties, but our basic attraction is simple; it's shiny; it's decadent; it's beautiful. These adjectives go without saying on this special edition of the iconic Air Max 97, as it takes over the bottom half of the shoe to make every step precious. In the dark, it still shines; the White, top half of the upper features reflective elements to ensure standing out is never off the table.

body.title: Nike Air Max 97

body.title: Nike Air Footscape Mid Utility DM
body.description: The Nike Air Footscape Mid Utility DM Men's Shoe rethinks a classic design with a quick-lacing system, adjustable collar and textile upper.

body.title: Nike Air Force 270 Utility
body.description: From the bottom of the bulbous Air Max 270 heel to the tippy-top of the zippered tongue, the Air Force 270 Utility delivers a dynamic look outfitted to take on bad weather with badass attitude. It's crafted with TecTuff material resistant to water and abrasions, and its waffle-inspired rubber coverage on the outsole provides durable traction whether you're on-road, or off. A midfoot buckle keeps everything secure, drops extra style, and offers an irreverent message. Check out the whole stomping force in Black and Volt.

body.title: Nike Cortez Basic Leather
body.description: The Nike Cortez Basic Leather is inspired by the 1972 original. Although it has gone through many incarnations, this version features premium leather for a return to the style icon's roots.

body.title: Nike Air Max 95
body.description: Taking inspiration from the classic layered look of a leather jacket over a fleece hoodie, the Nike Air Max 95 is ready to brave the elements this autumn. Quite possibly the perfect expression of a layered look, the shoe’s upper features leather, textile and mesh atop the famous visible Air units the 95 is known for.

body.title: Nike Air Max 97 NRG
body.description: Taking inspiration from the classic layered look of a hoodie and flannel, the Nike Air Max 97 is ready to brave the elements this autumn. Adding to the cozy effect is a suede plaid upper riding atop the visible full-length air unit the Air Max 97 is known for. A small reflective swoosh with help you stand out in a crowd ever so slightly.

body.title: Air Jordan 1 Retro High Strap
body.description: The latest N7 collection features a new iteration of the Air Jordan I Strap, which arrives set in the collection's key tones and prints inspired by the art of outstanding native and aboriginal athletes. The N7 collection supports Nike’s commitment to get kids moving through the N7 Fund, which supports organizations to provide sport and physical activity programming to kids in Native American and Aboriginal communities. Since its inception in 2009, the N7 Fund has awarded $5.6 million in grants to 243 communities and organizations, reaching more than 420,000 youth.

body.title: Nike Air Force 1 Premium
body.description: The latest N7 collection features a new iteration of the Air Force 1 Premium, which arrives set in the collection's key tones and prints inspired by the art of outstanding native and aboriginal athletes. body.title: Air Jordan 12 Retro
body.description: On September 12, 1996, MJ travelled to Tokyo with some of the league's best for the Hoop Heroes basketball clinic. In front of 32,000 fans, he showed off his skills in a series of 1-on-1s, challenged one of his teammates to a game of H-O-R-S-E, and took part in a friendly exhibition game against some of Japan's famous sumo wrestlers. The latest Air Jordan XII celebrates the event with a print inspired by the kimonos the wrestlers wore during the game.

body.title: Air Jordan 3 Retro WMNS
body.description: The latest Air Jordan III pushes the fashion-forward look of the silhouette even further. It upgrades the III’s typical construction with rich, tumbled leather and full-grain nubuck. A tonal Bordeaux shade helps the craftsmanship shine.

body.title: Nike Air Force 1
body.description:
In 1988, one of the world’s most recognizable slogans was coined. It was an ode to fitness and courage that has since inspired athletes across the globe to run faster, jump higher, and push past their potential, no matter the obstacles in their path.
This year, the tagline turns 30.
To celebrate the anniversary, this special-edition Air Force 1 Premium from the Just Do It Collection features the tagline’s original font and graphics from its 1988 debut. The shoe also comes with a rubber keychain that draws inspiration from an iconic poster printed the same year.

body.title: Nike LeBron 16
body.description: LeBron knows the amount of hard work and dedication it takes to dominate a sport. That’s why his appreciation for excellence permeates through the other sports he plays, every team he cheers for, and the fellow athletes he supports. Inspired by the Nike Air Trainer, a shoe created to support multiple athletic arenas, LeBron’s passion for sport shines through in the LeBron 16 'Air Trainer.'

body.title: Nike Blazer Mid '77
body.description: Nike’s first basketball shoe was worn by some of the greatest players on the court during the ‘70s and ‘80s. Since then, the Nike Blazer has been updated with various colorways and materials and this latest iteration refreshes the classic silhouette with a canvas upper for modern style.

body.title: Nike Air Max 95 WMNS
body.description: Celebrate sustainability without sacrificing style this summer. Inspired by alternative ways to make color, this special-edition Air Max 95 utilizes a natural, plant-based dye. The silhouette’s elegant design exemplifies new ways to approach color and material innovation with its reworked canvas upper and neutral, earth-esque palette.

body.title: Nike Air Max 1
body.description: Last year, Nike invited locals in New York City, London, Paris, Seoul, Shanghai, and Tokyo to design their own Nike Air Max inspired by the uniqueness of their communities. From these “On Air” workshops, 18 finalists were chosen based on the creative executions of their designs. The public then voted on six winners, one per city, which included Yuta Takuman from Tokyo.

body.title: Nike Air Foamposite |Preschool|
body.description: The three-year endeavor to develop the Foamposite was pure experimentation and imagination because, well, there was no brief to start with. Its seamless, unorthodox design has been featured in various bold, iridescent colors but this release has a unique ability—color shifting. When hit by sunlight, the silhouette appears to change colors for some extra flair on your feet this summer.

body.title: Nike Adapt BB
body.description: Designed to give you a customized, consistent fit, the Nike Adapt BB is our first power lacing shoe that's built for basketball. Strong yet flexible, it adapts to your foot to provide a locked-in feel for distraction-free play. Pair it with the Nike Adapt app to fine-tune the fit and customize the features from your smartphone.

body.title: Nike Air Max2 Light
body.description: In collaboration with Japanese-based brand atmos, this special-edition Air Max2 Light takes inspiration from Nike apparel in the ’90s and the upper is a twist on the bright, bold gear. A swoosh or “NIKE AIR” branding is printed or embroidered on every piece of patchwork, and each shoe features asymmetrical patterns. Take the aggressive design and transcend your individual, unique style.

body.title: Air Jordan 1 Low
body.description: Inspired by the 1985 original AJ1, the Air Jordan 1 Low Shoe offers a clean, classic look in a low-cut model that's perfect for casual wear.

body.title: Air Jordan 12 Retro WMNS
body.description: Celebrating Jordan Women’s ongoing theme of incorporating exotic materials on classic silhouettes, this AJ XII features multiple faux reptile materials on its upper. Gold accents deliver a premium aesthetic, and a “QUALITY INSPIRED BY THE GREATEST PLAYER EVER” text on the heel pays tribute to MJ’s championship pedigree.

body.title: Nike LeBron 16
body.description: For LeBron, the hardest he’s ever laughed is from watching Martin Lawrence’s hit ’90s sitcom “Martin.” Inspired by his love for the show, the LeBron 16 ‘Martin’ rekindles laugh-inducing memories with notable catch phrases on the back heel and styling reminiscent of the sitcom’s lively introduction.

body.title: Nike LeBron 16 Low
body.description: Inspired by the LeBron 3 'Remix' – a player exclusive that blended multiple LeBron silhouettes into one – the LeBron 16 'Remix' is a new premium concept come to life for all fans. It combines OG details with modern designs for a new take on the classic.

body.title: Nike Air Max2 Light
body.description: Since its arrival, Air Max has transformed Nike from the inside out, while revolutionizing the footwear industry at the same time. Originally introduced in 1994, the Air Max2 Light makes its return with an upper that blends synthetic and mesh materials. A soft foam midsole provides modern comfort, while the molded heel construction nods to the original for a ‘90s aesthetic.

body.title: Nike Air Trainer 3
body.description: Made for multi-sport play and inspired by athletes who excel both on and off the court, the Air Trainer 3 ‘Medicine Ball’ returns in classic form. Sporting an iconic strap and OG colors, the Air Trainer 3 remains ready for domination on all surfaces.

body.title: Nike PG 3
body.description: For PG, his game became truly elite only after he found his own Mamba Mentality. Taking cues from Kobe, PG’s Mamba Mentality drove his relentless training as well as guiding the development of his cold-blooded play. The PG 3 'Mamba Mentality' honors Kobe’s motivating impact on PG and how now, his own driven mindset is shaping his legacy.
